      <body>
         <listPerson>
            <person xml:id="pers2182">
               <p><persName>Martha (&apos;Patty</persName>&apos;) was born to <persName><ptr
                        target="/persons/pers2188.xml"/>Samuel Wesley</persName> and <persName><ptr
                        target="/persons/pers2193.xml"/>Susanna (Annesley) Wesley</persName> in
                     <placeName>Epworth</placeName> on <date when="1706-05-08">May 8, 1706</date>.
                  In the early <date>1730s</date> she lived at times in
                     <placeName>London</placeName> with her uncle <persName><ptr
                        target="/persons/pers2185.xml"/>Matthew Wesley</persName>. It was there that
                  she first met <persName><ptr target="/persons/pers0911.xml"/>Westley
                     Hall</persName>, one of <persName><ptr target="/persons/pers2180.xml"
                     />JW</persName>&apos;s Oxford students. <persName><ptr
                        target="/persons/pers0911.xml"/>Hall</persName> proved an ambivalent suitor,
                  courting both <persName>Martha</persName> and her sister <persName><ptr
                        target="/persons/pers2181.xml"/>Kezia</persName>. After their marriage on
                     <date when="1735-09-13">Sept. 13, 1735</date>, <persName><ptr
                        target="/persons/pers0911.xml"/>Hall</persName> proved equally unfaithful as
                  a husband and a pastor, deserting <persName>Martha</persName> for another woman in
                  the parish. <persName>Martha</persName> and their one surviving child, a son named
                        <persName><ptr target="/persons/pers0912.xml"/>Westley</persName>, were left
                  dependent upon support from extended family. <persName>Martha</persName>
                  eventually moved to <placeName>London</placeName>, where she lived with her sister
                        <persName><ptr target="/persons/pers2179.xml"/>Emilia</persName> and joined
                  in Methodist worship and ministry until her death on <date when="1791-07-12">July
                     12, 1791</date>. See Clarke, <hi rend="italic">Memoirs</hi> (1823, 511–37;
                  1836, 2:319–70, 1848, 558–97); and Maser, <hi rend="italic">Sisters</hi>,
                  79–101.</p>
            </person>
         </listPerson>
      </body>
   </text>
